adjectives.description: oriented (comparative more oriented, superlative most oriented)

entries.meaning: Having a specific orientation (positioning or direction).
examples: During assembly, keep the tab oriented toward the slot that it will later enter.

entries.meaning: (often with with or in) Having had an orientation (an introduction to a topic or place).
examples: They are now oriented with the main campus.
I am no expert in geometry, but I am suitably oriented in it.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of orient
